## 5. Keybindings — primary input

### 5.1. Conventions

Choose one и follow:

| Style | Examples | App examples |
|---|---|---|
| **vim-like** | h/j/k/l для navigation; `:command`; `/search` | vim, less, lazygit |
| **emacs-like** | C-n / C-p; M-x command; C-s search | emacs, slack-term |
| **arrow-key + modern** | Arrows для nav; `?` для help; Esc для cancel | htop, k9s |

Mixing styles — confusing. Choose primary, optionally support secondary.

### 5.2. Universal keybindings (никогда не переопределяем)

| Key | Действие |
|---|---|
| `q` / `Esc` / `Ctrl+C` | Quit / cancel |
| `?` / `F1` | Help / cheat sheet |
| `Enter` | Activate / select |
| `Tab` / `Shift+Tab` | Cycle focus |
| Arrow keys | Navigation |
| `/` | Search (vim-style) или Ctrl+F (modern) |
| `Ctrl+L` | Redraw screen |

### 5.3. Disclosure

`?` обязательно показывает modal / panel с keybindings. **Никогда** скрытые keybindings без discovery mechanism.

Inline hints в status bar: `[q] Quit  [?] Help  [/] Search`.

### 5.4. Mouse support

Optional но nice. `set -g mouse on` в tmux era ожидается. Click для selection / scroll wheel для scrolling. Никогда **только** mouse — keyboard primary.

